It wasn't something people wanted.
As the pilot project continued, the American Civil Liberties Union of Nevada warned on its website: "It would be very easy to turn these devices into full-fledged surveillance devices".
There is no need to build a huge, cumbersome technological infrastructure that will inevitably extend to recording the daily comings and goings of individuals.
Nevada is one of the few states that is trying to find available technology that would allow the state to track how many miles a vehicle has traveled, but not exactly when and where.
