The dispute comes as the aircraft manufacturers are competing to sell the largest version of their twin-engine long-range aircraft with a potential record number of orders expected during the event from November 17 to 21.
The way the rear of the aircraft is arranged, particularly whether there are 9 or 10 seats side by side, is the basis of the economic performance claims for new mini-jumbo aircraft designs.
Boeing says the upgraded 777X will carry 406 people in economy seats more than 17 inches [43 cm] wide, spread out 10 in each row.
