Msgr. Alena Šmídová graduated from the Secondary Medical School in the field of Health Nurse (graduated in 1978) and the Faculty of Philosophy of Charles University in Prague in the study program Nursing - Pedagogy (graduated in 1992).
Since 2010, she has been head of the Department of Nursing and Other Non-Medical Specialties and Recognition of Qualifications at the Ministry of Education and Science.
During her professional career, she worked as a bedside nurse in the internal department, and also worked as a teacher at the Central Medical School, where she was also a statutory deputy director for 8 years.
From 2004 to 2009, she worked as a chief nurse of the Prison Service of the Czech Republic.
She published several professional nursing textbooks and articles in professional journals, and was engaged in lecturing in the field of nursing.
She is not a member of any political party.
